<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>CPT Gate Instrument</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"/>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin/>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@300;400;500&family=Barlow:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>

<style>
:root {
  --bg: #0c0c0b;
  --surface: #141412;
  --surface2: #1c1c19;
  --border: #2a2a26;
  --border-bright: #3d3d38;
  --text: #e8e4dc;
  --text-dim: #7a7670;
  --text-mid: #b0ab9f;
  --green: #4a7c6f;
  --green-bright: #6aaa98;
  --green-dim: #2c4a3e;
  --red: #8c3a2e;
  --red-bright: #c25040;
  --red-dim: #4a1f18;
  --amber: #8c6a1a;
  --amber-bright: #c49030;
  --mono: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
  --serif: 'Libre Baskerville', Georgia, serif;
  --sans: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
}

*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

body {
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
  font-family: var(--sans);
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

/* ── HEADER ── */
header {
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
  position: relative;
}

header::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -1px; left: 0;
  width: 180px; height: 2px;
  background: var(--green);
}

.header-inner {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 2rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 2rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.header-left {}

.inst-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.2em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--green-bright);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

h1 {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--text);
  line-height: 1.2;
}

h1 em {
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--green-bright);
}

.header-desc {
  margin-top: 0.6rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  max-width: 480px;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.header-right {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: flex-end;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.gate-status {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-bright);
  color: var(--text-dim);
  background: var(--surface);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.gate-status.pass { border-color: var(--green); color: var(--green-bright); background: var(--green-dim); }
.gate-status.fail { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red-bright); background: var(--red-dim); }

/* ── MAIN ── */
main {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 2rem 6rem;
}

/* ── PROGRESS BAR ── */
.progress-track {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
  background: var(--bg);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 0.75rem 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.progress-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  white-space: nowrap;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.progress-dots {
  display: flex;
  gap: 4px;
  align-items: center;
}

.dot {
  width: 6px; height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--border-bright);
  transition: background 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.dot.active { background: var(--green); transform: scale(1.3); }
.dot.complete { background: var(--green-dim); border: 1px solid var(--green); }
.dot.failed { background: var(--red-dim); border: 1px solid var(--red); }
.dot.current { background: var(--amber-bright); transform: scale(1.3); }

/* ── SECTION INTRO ── */
.section-intro-block {
  margin: 3rem 0 2rem;
  padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.section-intro-block h2 {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.section-intro-block p {
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ── SYSTEM DEFINITION ── */
.system-def {
  margin: 2.5rem 0;
  display: grid;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.field-group {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}

.field-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.62rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.field-input {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  color: var(--text);
  font-family: var(--sans);
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  padding: 0.65rem 0.9rem;
  outline: none;
  transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  width: 100%;
}

.field-input:focus { border-color: var(--green); }
.field-input::placeholder { color: var(--text-dim); opacity: 0.5; }

textarea.field-input { resize: vertical; min-height: 70px; }

/* ── AXIOM MODULES ── */
.axiom-module {
  margin: 2rem 0;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: var(--surface);
  transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
  opacity: 0.4;
  pointer-events: none;
  transition: opacity 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease;
}

.axiom-module.unlocked {
  opacity: 1;
  pointer-events: all;
}

.axiom-module.complete-pass { border-color: var(--green-dim); }
.axiom-module.complete-fail { border-color: var(--red); }
.axiom-module.active-module { border-color: var(--amber); }

.axiom-header {
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 1rem;
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;
}

.axiom-num-badge {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  color: var(--green-bright);
  background: var(--green-dim);
  padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 2px;
}

.axiom-title-text {
  flex: 1;
}

.axiom-name {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
}

.axiom-sub {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  font-family: var(--mono);
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.axiom-score-display {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: flex-end;
  gap: 0.2rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.s-value {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  transition: color 0.3s ease;
}

.s-value.good { color: var(--green-bright); }
.s-value.warn { color: var(--amber-bright); }
.s-value.bad { color: var(--red-bright); }

.d-value {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.d-value.pass { color: var(--green); }
.d-value.fail { color: var(--red-bright); }

/* ── QUESTIONS ── */
.axiom-body {
  padding: 1.5rem;
  display: none;
}

.axiom-body.open { display: block; }

.question-block {
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.question-block:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
  margin-bottom: 0;
  padding-bottom: 0;
}

.question-text {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  color: var(--text-mid);
  line-height: 1.55;
  margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
}

.question-context {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  font-style: italic;
  margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  margin-top: -0.5rem;
}

/* Response buttons */
.response-options {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.resp-btn {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  padding: 0.45rem 0.9rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-bright);
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.15s ease;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.resp-btn:hover {
  border-color: var(--green-bright);
  color: var(--green-bright);
}

.resp-btn.selected-yes {
  background: var(--green-dim);
  border-color: var(--green);
  color: var(--green-bright);
}

.resp-btn.selected-partial {
  background: #2a2010;
  border-color: var(--amber);
  color: var(--amber-bright);
}

.resp-btn.selected-no {
  background: var(--red-dim);
  border-color: var(--red);
  color: var(--red-bright);
}

/* ── DRIFT BAR ── */
.drift-bar-container {
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  padding-top: 1.25rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.drift-bar-label {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.drift-bar-label span {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.drift-track {
  height: 4px;
  background: var(--border);
  position: relative;
}

.drift-fill {
  height: 100%;
  background: var(--green);
  transition: width 0.4s ease, background 0.4s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.threshold-marker {
  position: absolute;
  top: -4px;
  width: 2px;
  height: 12px;
  background: var(--amber-bright);
}

/* ── GATE RESULT ── */
#gate-result {
  display: none;
  margin: 3rem 0;
  border: 2px solid var(--border);
  padding: 2rem;
  background: var(--surface2);
}

#gate-result.pass { border-color: var(--green); }
#gate-result.fail { border-color: var(--red); }

.gate-verdict {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  font-weight: 400;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.gate-verdict.pass { color: var(--green-bright); }
.gate-verdict.fail { color: var(--red-bright); }

.gate-verdict-sub {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.axiom-summary-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.axiom-summary-item {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 0.75rem;
  background: var(--surface);
}

.asi-name {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
}

.asi-score {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 1rem;
}

.asi-score.pass { color: var(--green-bright); }
.asi-score.fail { color: var(--red-bright); }
.asi-score.warn { color: var(--amber-bright); }

.asi-d {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.gate-narrative {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  color: var(--text-mid);
  line-height: 1.65;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding-top: 1.25rem;
}

/* ── ACTIONS ── */
.action-row {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.btn {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
  border: 1px solid;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  background: transparent;
}

.btn-primary {
  border-color: var(--green);
  color: var(--green-bright);
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background: var(--green-dim);
}

.btn-secondary {
  border-color: var(--border-bright);
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.btn-secondary:hover {
  border-color: var(--text-dim);
  color: var(--text-mid);
}

/* ── REJECTION FLAGS ── */
.rejection-flags {
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
}

.rejection-flag {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
  padding: 0.75rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--red-dim);
  background: var(--red-dim);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.rf-icon {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  color: var(--red-bright);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  padding-top: 1px;
}

.rf-text {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--text-mid);
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.rf-text strong {
  color: var(--red-bright);
  font-weight: 500;
}

/* ── FOOTER ── */
footer {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

.footer-l, .footer-r {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

/* ── COMPLETE BANNER ── */
.complete-banner {
  display: none;
  background: var(--green-dim);
  border: 1px solid var(--green);
  padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.62rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--green-bright);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
</style>

</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="header-inner">
    <div class="header-left">
      <div class="inst-label">Condition Preservation Theory · Gate Instrument v0.1</div>
      <h1>CPT <em>Gate</em><br>Instrument</h1>
      <p class="header-desc">Structural admissibility diagnostic. Observable indicators derive s<sub>i</sub> state values — no direct self-scoring. If any axiom breaches threshold τ<sub>i</sub>, system is non-admissible under CPT.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="header-right">
      <div class="gate-status" id="header-gate-status">AWAITING INPUT</div>
      <div style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.55rem; color: var(--text-dim); margin-top: 0.25rem;">8 axioms · 6 rejection conditions</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main>

  <!-- STICKY PROGRESS -->

  <div class="progress-track">
    <span class="progress-label">AXIOM PROGRESS</span>
    <div class="progress-dots" id="progress-dots"></div>
    <span class="progress-label" id="progress-fraction" style="margin-left: auto;">0 / 8</span>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 1: SYSTEM DEFINITION -->

  <div class="section-intro-block" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
    <h2>Step 1 — System Definition</h2>
    <p>Identify the system under evaluation. Specificity improves diagnostic accuracy. Vague definitions produce unreliable s<sub>i</sub> readings.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="system-def">
    <div class="field-group">
      <label class="field-label" for="sys-name">System name or identifier</label>
      <input class="field-input" id="sys-name" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Municipal waste management authority, Regional health trust, Platform cooperative"/>
    </div>
    <div class="field-group">
      <label class="field-label" for="sys-purpose">Declared purpose</label>
      <textarea class="field-input" id="sys-purpose" placeholder="What does the system claim to do? State this in its own terms."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="field-group">
      <label class="field-label" for="sys-domain">Domain</label>
      <input class="field-input" id="sys-domain" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Public health, Housing, Energy, Finance, Governance"/>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
      <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="beginDiagnostic()">Begin Axiom Diagnostic →</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 2: AXIOM MODULES -->

  <div class="section-intro-block" id="axiom-section-header" style="display:none;">
    <h2>Step 2 — Axiom Diagnostic Modules</h2>
    <p>Answer each question based on observable, structural evidence about the system — not your opinion of it. The instrument computes s<sub>i</sub> from your responses.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="axiom-modules"></div>

  <!-- STEP 3: GATE RESULT -->

  <div id="gate-result">
    <div id="gate-verdict-text" class="gate-verdict"></div>
    <div id="gate-verdict-sub" class="gate-verdict-sub"></div>
    <div class="axiom-summary-grid" id="axiom-summary-grid"></div>
    <div id="rejection-flags-container" class="rejection-flags"></div>
    <div class="gate-narrative" id="gate-narrative"></div>
    <div class="action-row">
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="resetInstrument()">Reset & Re-evaluate</button>
      <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="window.print()">Export Report</button>
    </div>
  </div>

</main>

<footer>
  <span class="footer-l">CPT GATE INSTRUMENT · PHASE 2 BEHAVIORAL SIMULATOR</span>
  <span class="footer-r">Field &amp; Signal · Condition Preservation Theory</span>
</footer>

<script>
// ── AXIOM DEFINITIONS ──
const AXIOMS = [
  {
    id: 1,
    name: "Regeneration as Hard Constraint",
    sub: "Axiom 01 · τ₁ = 0.35",
    tau: 0.35,
    rejectionLabel: "Unbounded Cost Displacement",
    questions: [
      {
        text: "Are the primary inputs this system depends on (materials, labor, attention, ecological conditions) being replenished at a rate equal to or greater than consumption?",
        context: "Consider the full input chain, not just immediate operational inputs.",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No", "Unknown"]
      },
      {
        text: "Does the system have a mechanism that triggers intervention when input depletion rates exceed recovery rates?",
        context: "A mechanism that exists on paper but isn't enforced scores as Partial.",
        options: ["Yes", "Partial", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Can the system continue operating in its current form for the next 20 years without fundamentally depleting the conditions it depends on?",
        context: "This is a structural projection question, not an aspiration question.",
        options: ["Yes", "Uncertain", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Are depletion rates for core inputs measured and reported within the system's own accountability structure?",
        options: ["Yes, regularly", "Occasionally", "No"]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    name: "Externalities Internalized",
    sub: "Axiom 02 · τ₂ = 0.40",
    tau: 0.40,
    rejectionLabel: "Non-Observable Dependency Structure",
    questions: [
      {
        text: "Are negative outcomes of system operation — environmental damage, labor strain, community disruption — tracked within the same accounting structure that measures system benefits?",
        context: "If benefits are tracked in one system and harms in another (or not at all), score No.",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "When harm occurs, is it formally attributed to the system that produced it?",
        context: "Attribution means the cost is assigned, not just acknowledged.",
        options: ["Yes", "Sometimes", "No", "Not applicable"]
      },
      {
        text: "Do externalized costs feed back into decision-making about system operation?",
        context: "Check whether harm data changes how decisions are made, not just whether it is collected.",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Are there populations or ecosystems that bear costs from this system but have no representation in its governance structure?",
        options: ["No (all affected parties represented)", "Some gaps", "Yes, significantly"]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    name: "Signal Integrity",
    sub: "Axiom 03 · τ₃ = 0.30",
    tau: 0.30,
    rejectionLabel: "Feedback Suppression or Distortion",
    questions: [
      {
        text: "When negative outcomes occur, are they recorded in the same system that receives rewards for positive outcomes?",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Can operators suppress, delay, or selectively report failure data without formal consequence?",
        options: ["No", "In some conditions", "Yes"]
      },
      {
        text: "Are the metrics used to evaluate success independently auditable by parties with no stake in the outcome?",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Does the system reward accurate reporting of failure as much as it rewards positive performance?",
        context: "Look at incentive structures, not stated values.",
        options: ["Yes", "Neutral", "No — success is rewarded, failure is penalized"]
      },
      {
        text: "Is there a structural mechanism by which people inside the system can raise concerns about its effects without career or operational risk?",
        options: ["Yes, protected", "Informally tolerated", "No"]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    name: "Throughput Within Adaptive Capacity",
    sub: "Axiom 04 · τ₄ = 0.35",
    tau: 0.35,
    rejectionLabel: "Throughput Exceeds Adaptive Capacity at Baseline",
    questions: [
      {
        text: "Is the system's current operational load within the range it was designed to handle coherently?",
        context: "Not maximum capacity — coherent handling. Signs of incoherence: decisions made without full information, errors attributed to volume rather than error.",
        options: ["Yes", "At the edge", "No — operating beyond coherent range"]
      },
      {
        text: "When the system scales (grows, adds users, expands mandate), does it have formal mechanisms for checking whether adaptive capacity keeps pace?",
        options: ["Yes", "Ad hoc", "No"]
      },
      {
        text: "Has the system experienced breakdown, error cascades, or coordination failures in the past 2 years attributable to scale rather than isolated incident?",
        options: ["No", "Isolated incidents", "Yes, repeatedly"]
      },
      {
        text: "Is decision velocity (how fast decisions must be made) matched by the system's ability to gather and process the information required to make them well?",
        options: ["Yes", "Sometimes mismatched", "Chronic mismatch"]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 5,
    name: "Power Revisability",
    sub: "Axiom 05 · τ₅ = 0.40",
    tau: 0.40,
    rejectionLabel: "Irreversible Power Asymmetry",
    questions: [
      {
