        context: "This is a historical track record question.",
        options: ["No documented cases", "Possibly, unclear", "Yes — documented cases"]
      },
      {
        text: "Does the system reward behaviors that generate internal metric performance at the expense of the broader conditions it depends on?",
        options: ["No", "In some cases", "Yes — systematically"]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 8,
    name: "Early Collapse Signal Legibility",
    sub: "Axiom 08 · τ₈ = 0.30",
    tau: 0.30,
    rejectionLabel: "Collapse Signal Illegibility",
    questions: [
      {
        text: "Are early-stage degradation signals (not just crisis-level failures) visible within the system's monitoring infrastructure?",
        context: "If the first signal is a crisis, early warning is absent.",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No — only crisis-level signals are tracked"]
      },
      {
        text: "When early warnings are generated, are they actionable — do they trigger decisions before conditions become critical?",
        options: ["Yes", "Sometimes", "No — warnings are generated but not acted on"]
      },
      {
        text: "Is there a documented history of the system successfully responding to early degradation signals before they became crises?",
        options: ["Yes", "Unclear record", "No — responses are typically reactive"]
      },
      {
        text: "Can individuals inside the system act on early collapse signals without waiting for formal authorization from the level that might be producing them?",
        context: "If the signal is that leadership is failing, can anyone below leadership act on that?",
        options: ["Yes", "Partially", "No — action requires authorization from potential source of failure"]
